SIMPLE: dissecting
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dissecting
<hw>Dis*sect"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Dividing or
separating the parts of an animal or vegetable body; <as>as, a
<ex>dissecting</ex> aneurism, one which makes its way between or within
the coats of an artery</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to, or received during, a
dissection; <as>as, a <ex>dissecting</ex> wound</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Used for or in dissecting; <as>as, a
<ex>dissecting</ex> knife; a <ex>dissecting</ex>
microscope.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dissection</ent>⟦br⟧
